        "id": 1066743
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-20T15:41:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "also mentioned the \"running in the background\" thing, because that\u0027s something that doesn\u0027t necessarily follow from not-acting-as-init.\n\nAlso, isn\u0027t -I the one that governs the running-as-init thing? IIUC -i just does the orphaning part of the whole process tree:\n\n $ sudo out/host/linux-x86/bin/minijail0 -p -i -Tstatic -- /bin/bash -c \u0027echo $$\u0027\n 2\n $ sudo out/host/linux-x86/bin/minijail0 -p -i -I -Tstatic -- /bin/bash -c \u0027echo $$\u0027\n 1\n\nIf so, I think we should also amend the --help message.",
      "parentUuid": "f181880c_9602c515",
      "revId": "788e78750ffd500703bf9d12515ed1cf13e5fb14",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
