      "writtenOn": "2018-04-20T16:46:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think Jorge just mean \"act as init\" in so much that minijail waits for the child process and reaps things.  the -I init flag controls whether minijail is pid 1 inside the new pid namespace (and thus acts as a \"normal\" init) or the jailed process is pid 1.\n\n-i is for the very first minijail process only.",
      "parentUuid": "8c03b48f_c005cd8f",
